<br>
1.  Assinate is just fine the way it is.  It actually has some use in the game, though it's minor.<br>
<br>
2. Poisons are not for everyday xp.  They're for specific high level raid targets.  Making them everyday would be bad and would definitely unblance a ton of existing encounters.  You don't need them for xp.  You don't even really need them for raid targets, but for the raid targets, the existing effort vs. reward makes them quite viable already.<br>
<br>
3. Nix the better tanking for rogues.  You're tops at backline damage.  Learn not to flip things if you don't want to take damage.<br>
<br>
4. Nix the better resists for melee.  It's pretty easy to get 100 base in all resists just through gear.  If you work at it, you can top 170 in all resists.  Mine are about 150-180 in normal everyday fighting gear.  Get your resists up and you don't need any special babysitting to resist AE.<br>
<br>
5. Nice daggers are plentiful enough -- too plentiful.  I'm all for rogues doing good damage, but gearing 'em is easier than warrior or monk already.  Be nice if you could upgrade any epic to make it usuable in the charm slot, no way should the rogue epic be instantly range-slot.  It's one of the easiest epics to do and has great longevity.  It doesn't need more without making it a lot harder to attain.<br>
<br>
6. YES!  I like this one.  All the pure melee should get AAs similar to endless quiver.  It's not as if we'd do outrageous damage that way or even damage anywhere close to a ranger, but it would sure give us more options for our range slot.  This is really a monk problem and not a rogue, though.  Rogues and wars can use a primal bow, for instance, and have great stats and a nice pull toy all in one.<br>
<br>
